title: Barcelona vs Real Madrid - Spanish La Liga 2023/2024
description: Barcelona have won their last three matches against Real Madrid in all competitions, only once in the entire history of ElClásico, between 2008 and 2010 under Josep Guardiola, have the Blaugrana managed 4+ consecutive wins. title: PSG vs Auxerre - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 34
description: Paris SG have not lost any of their last five matches against Auxerre in Ligue 1. PSG are also unbeaten in their last 37 home games against a promoted side in Ligue 1 – scoring an average of 2.9 goals – since a defeat against Montpellier in their last match of the 2009-10 season. The last draw between Paris SG and Auxerre at the Parc des Princes in Ligue 1 was in December 2001. Since then, the 11 clashes between the two teams in the top-flight have seen eight wins for Paris and three for Auxerre.

title: Freiburg vs Eintracht Frankfurt - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 34
description: This fixture is SC Freiburg’s 850th Bundesliga match. They have only won one of their last 10 top-flight meetings with Eintracht Frankfurt and are winless in their last five, their longest ever wait for victory against the Eagles. SC Freiburg have picked up 13 of a possible 15 points over the last five matchdays, a joint league high together with Borussia Dortmund. Eintracht Frankfurt have also remained unbeaten during this period, conceding the joint-fewest goals in the league.

title: LaLiga BEST 11 - Luis García
description: Luis Garcia was a striker who played 8 seasons in La Liga. He played for Barcelona, Real Valladolid, Atletico Madrid and Real Racing in La Liga. In his career he played 473 games, scoring 115 goals.

title: Borussia Dortmund vs Holstein Kiel - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 34
description: Holstein Kiel and Borussia Dortmund have met three times so far: BVB won 4-0 away in the quarter-finals of the 2011/12 DFB-Pokal and then 5-0 at home in the semi-finals in 2020/21, before the Storks won 4-2 in this season’s reverse fixture. It was Dortmund’s first defeat against a Bundesliga debutant since August 2019. Borussia Dortmund have won four Bundesliga games in a row for the first time since March 2024. They have picked up 19 of a possible 21 points from the last seven matchdays, a league high.

title: Borussia Monchengladbach vs Wolfsburg - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 34
description: VfL Wolfsburg recorded their joint-biggest win in the Bundesliga this season in the reverse fixture against Borussia Monchengladbach – the Wolves could now do a league double over the Foals for the first time since 2009/10. VfL Wolfsburg are winless in their last nine Bundesliga games, the longest ongoing wait in the league and the Wolves’ longest spell without victory since between December 2023 and March 2024. Wolfsburg are also without a clean sheet in their last 12 Bundesliga matches, currently the worst run in the league.

title: LaLiga Power Ep.8
description: LALIGA Power is a program that pays tribute to all those who inspire the world through the values of football. title: Olympique Marseille vs Rennes - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 34
description: Marseille have won three of their last four home games against Rennes in Ligue 1, each time without conceding a single goal. OM have kept 12 clean sheets at home against SRFC in the 21st century, at least two more than against any other team during this period. Marseille have finished just one of the last 12 Ligue 1 seasons with a defeat, losing 1-0 at Ajaccio on 3 June 2023.

description: Everyone knows the biggest stadiums in the world. But sometimes its the smallest stadiums that are the most intimidating for players, due to their fans and their fervor. title: RB Leipzig vs Stuttgart - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 34
description: Including this season’s DFB-Pokal semi-final, VfB Stuttgart have won each of their last three competitive games against RB Leipzig. The Swabians have lost all six of their Bundesliga away matches to date against RB Leipzig – in league history, only Kickers Offenbach have played more away games at one opponent without ever collecting at least a point. 51 points from 33 games represents RB Leipzig’s second-worst Bundesliga season – they have only been worse off at this stage in 2017/18. 13 wins from 33 games is also their lowest tally ever in the top flight. The Red Bulls could also now endure a five-game winless run for the first time in the Bundesliga.

title: St. Pauli vs Bochum - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 34
description: FC St. Pauli are currently winless in their last six competitive games against VfL Bochum, though they are unbeaten in all five of their top-flight home games against them. St. Pauli haven’t faced any other side as often at home in the Bundesliga without losing at least once. FC St. Pauli are three points and 13 goals ahead of 1. FC Heidenheim going into the final matchday, meaning a point would be enough to guarantee their survival. St. Pauli last avoided relegation in a top-flight season all the way back in 1995/96.

title: In The Footsteps of Marquinhos - Ligue 1 Documentary 2024/25
description: From Brazil to France, beIN tells you the impressive journey of the Captain of Paris Saint-Germain. With 300 Ligue 1 matches recently played, discover the story of Marquinhos!

title: Olympique Marseille vs Rennes - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 34
description: Marseille have won three of their last four home games against Rennes in Ligue 1, each time without conceding a single goal. Marseille have finished just one of the last 12 Ligue 1 seasons with a defeat, losing 1-0 at Ajaccio on 3 June 2023.

title: Strasbourg vs Le Havre - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 34
description: The 39 meetings between Strasbourg and Le Havre in Ligue 1 have produced only three draws, a ratio of 7.7%. This is the lowest percentage of draws between two Ligue 1 teams among those who have faced each other 20+ times. Strasbourg have lost their last three matches to finish a Ligue 1 season, but they have been away from home each time, at Marseille, Lorient and Lyon in the last three years. At home, RCSA have gone three games to close a season without losing.

title: Saint-Étienne vs Toulouse - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 34
description: St Etienne have lost only one of their last nine matches against Toulouse in Ligue 1, it was this season in the reverse fixture; a 2-1 win for TFC at home in December. St Etienne have won just one of their last seven matches to finish a Ligue 1 season, 5-0 against Lille in 2017-18.

title: Nantes vs Montpellier - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 34
description: Nantes have won 64.3% of their Ligue 1 home games against Montpellier in the 21st century, their highest success rate against an opponent they have faced 10+ times on home soil during this period. Since their return to the top-flight in 2013-14, Nantes have finished just two of their last 11 Ligue 1 campaigns with a victory : 1-0 v Strasbourg in 2017-18 and 1-0 v Angers in 2022-23.

title: Nantes vs Montpellier - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 34

title: Borussia Dortmund vs Holstein Kiel - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 34
description: Holstein Kiel and Borussia Dortmund have met three times so far: BVB won 4-0 away in the quarter-finals of the 2011/12 DFB-Pokal and then 5-0 at home in the semi-finals in 2020/21, before the Storks won 4-2 in this season’s reverse fixture. It was Dortmund’s first defeat against a Bundesliga debutant since August 2019. Borussia Dortmund have won four Bundesliga games in a row for the first time since March 2024. They have picked up 19 of a possible 21 points from the last seven matchdays, a league high.

title: Borussia Monchengladbach vs Wolfsburg - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 34
description: VfL Wolfsburg recorded their joint-biggest win in the Bundesliga this season in the reverse fixture against Borussia Monchengladbach – the Wolves could now do a league double over the Foals for the first time since 2009/10. VfL Wolfsburg are winless in their last nine Bundesliga games, the longest ongoing wait in the league and the Wolves’ longest spell without victory since between December 2023 and March 2024. Wolfsburg are also without a clean sheet in their last 12 Bundesliga matches, currently the worst run in the league.

TSG have won just one of their last nine league games : 2-0 at home against Mainz in mid-April.

title: Stadium of Fears
description: Everyone knows the biggest stadiums in the world. But sometimes its the smallest stadiums that are the most intimidating for players, due to their fans and their fervor. Several big names in football tell you about their experiences in these stadiums where it can sometimes be difficult to play.

title: Borussia Monchengladbach vs Wolfsburg - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 34
description: VfL Wolfsburg recorded their joint-biggest win in the Bundesliga this season in the reverse fixture against Borussia Monchengladbach – the Wolves could now do a league double over the Foals for the first time since 2009/10. VfL Wolfsburg are winless in their last nine Bundesliga games, the longest ongoing wait in the league and the Wolves’ longest spell without victory since between December 2023 and March 2024. Wolfsburg are also without a clean sheet in their last 12 Bundesliga matches, currently the worst run in the league.

title: Freiburg vs Eintracht Frankfurt - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 34
description: This fixture is SC Freiburg’s 850th Bundesliga match. They have only won one of their last 10 top-flight meetings with Eintracht Frankfurt and are winless in their last five, their longest ever wait for victory against the Eagles. SC Freiburg have picked up 13 of a possible 15 points over the last five matchdays, a joint league high together with Borussia Dortmund. Eintracht Frankfurt have also remained unbeaten during this period, conceding the joint-fewest goals in the league.

description: Lille have won two games in a row against Reims in Ligue 1, after failing to win any of the previous four. LOSC could string together three wins against Reims for the second time in their top-flight history, after August 2020-September 2021. Reims have conceded at least one goal in each of their last 13 away games against Lille in Ligue 1, the longest run of its kind for SdR against a current top-flight team.

description: 1. FSV Mainz 05 have lost 11 of their 14 Bundesliga games against Bayer 04 Leverkusen since the start of 2018 – the Werkself haven’t beaten any other side more often during this period and the 05ers haven’t suffered more defeats against any other side. Leverkusen have won each of the last three meetings. Bayer 04 Leverkusen have only won one of their last five Bundesliga games. 68 points from 33 games is still their third-best record in the top flight. Last weekend’s 4-2 defeat against Borussia Dortmund saw them concede more than three goals in a Bundesliga game for the first time since October 2022.

title: Nice vs Brest - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 34
description: Nice have lost only one of their last eight Ligue 1 games against Brest. The last five Nice-Brest matches in Ligue 1 have produced just three goals, or 0.6 per game, the lowest average among meetings played in each of the last three seasons. Nice have won five of their last six matches to finish a Ligue 1 season, sharing the points in their most recent one. The last defeat of OGCN to end a season in the top-flight dates to 2017-18.

title: PSG vs Auxerre - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 34
description: Paris SG have not lost any of their last five matches against Auxerre in Ligue 1. PSG are also unbeaten in their last 37 home games against a promoted side in Ligue 1 – scoring an average of 2.9 goals – since a defeat against Montpellier in their last match of the 2009-10 season. The last draw between Paris SG and Auxerre at the Parc des Princes in Ligue 1 was in December 2001. Since then, the 11 clashes between the two teams in the top-flight have seen eight wins for Paris and three for Auxerre.

title: Bundesliga - Ruhr Valley: The heart of German football
description: What characterises this extraordinary region? What makes clubs like Borussia Dortmund, FC Schalke 04 and VfL Bochum 1848 so special? We embark on an emotional journey through time and visit authentic locations in the Ruhr area. We bring the culture of this unique region to life. Alongside the two Ruhr legends and world champions Benedikt Howedes and Kevin GroSSkreutz, authentic protagonists work through great football moments from the history of the Ruhr region, which are interwoven with the sporting topicality of the 2024/25 Bundesliga season.

title: EPL Stories 2024/25 - Chris Wood
description: We follow New Zealand striker Chris Wood during a crucial World Cup Qualifier on home soll, at the peak of one of the most Impressive seasons of his career. Back in his hometown, we meet the family, coaches and friends who helped shape the player and the person hes become. From humble beginnings to Premier League mainstay, Wood reflects on the pressures hes faced, the pride of leading his country, and the mindset thats driven him every step of the way.

title: EPL The Big Interview 2024/25 - Daniel Muñoz
description: He didnt make it as a professional until he was 20 years old but always dreamt of playing for his boyhood dub, Atletico Nacional. Having realised that dream, Daniel Muñoz has enjoyed a brilliant first full season in South London and now has his sights on FA cup glory with Crystal Palace. The Colombian fans favourite speaks to The Big Interview this week about his rapid rise to the Premier League and how hes longing to give Eagles fans their first ever major trophy.

title: Strasbourg vs Le Havre - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 34
description: The 39 meetings between Strasbourg and Le Havre in Ligue 1 have produced only three draws, a ratio of 7.7%. This is the lowest percentage of draws between two Ligue 1 teams among those who have faced each other 20+ times. Strasbourg have lost their last three matches to finish a Ligue 1 season, but they have been away from home each time, at Marseille, Lorient and Lyon in the last three years. At home, RCSA have gone three games to close a season without losing.

title: Nantes vs Montpellier - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 34
description: Nantes have won 64.3% of their Ligue 1 home games against Montpellier in the 21st century, their highest success rate against an opponent they have faced 10+ times on home soil during this period. Since their return to the top-flight in 2013-14, Nantes have finished just two of their last 11 Ligue 1 campaigns with a victory : 1-0 v Strasbourg in 2017-18 and 1-0 v Angers in 2022-23.

title: Match 1 - ATP 250 Gonet Geneva Open - Switzerland 2025
description: The Gonet Geneva Open is a premier ATP 250 clay-court tournament held at the historic Tennis Club de Genève in Parc des Eaux-Vives. Celebrating its 10th anniversary in 2025, the event attracts top-tier talent as a key warm-up to Roland Garros. This years field features stars like Novak Djokovic, Taylor Fritz, and three-time champion Casper Ruud, promising a week of world-class tennis in a picturesque lakeside setting.
